# Hybrid-MMR Legal RAG System — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A clause-level legal retrieval system for the **Indian Penal Code (IPC)** combining BM25 sparse retrieval, dense vector embeddings, and MMR reranking into a single hybrid pipeline.

---

## Architecture

```
IPC PDF
  └─► extract_text.py        → raw text (pdfplumber + OCR fallback)
  └─► segment_clauses.py     → 455 IPC clauses (JSON)
  └─► augment_clauses.py     → enriched clause texts for 17 key sections

clauses_augmented.json
  ├─► vector_index.py        → FAISS IndexFlatIP (455 × 384 embeddings)
  └─► bm25_index.py          → BM25Okapi (rank_bm25)

Query
  ├─► baseline.py            → Vector-only retrieval (cosine sim)
  ├─► hybrid.py              → 0.6×vector + 0.4×BM25 (min-max normalised)
  └─► mmr.py                 → MMR reranking (λ=0.9) → top-5 results

evaluation/metrics.py        → Precision@5, Recall@5, MRR
app.py                       → Streamlit demo UI
main.py                      → CLI pipeline entry point
```

---

